<Review ID>4040057
<Product Name>Creative Zen Micro 5 GB MP3 Player Green
<Title>i love my purple zen micro!
<Date>Fri Nov 11 00:00:00 CST 2005
<Content>When I first received the Micro, I did have some very frustrating times with the touchpad.  Then all of a sudden, I got it.  While it certainly remains a little over-sensitive, I am very comfortable with it.  Buttons would be better and I see that the Zen touch has them.  So far (2 and 1/2 months) my earphone jack has not broken.  Today, I purchased the extended warranty sitting in my cart for $40.00 from Creative, but noticed it went up to $50.00.  That is a lot for a $179.00 item that when the new price points already are much lower for much more storage..But it seems that the odds are that something will go wrong with the jack and the player might freeze up.  Within the first few days of owning it, my player did freeze up.  I was only getting about 3 hours on the battery.  I called Creative and it was just a matter of taking the battery out and putting it back holding the power on the whole time (I forgot the term for that).  I also downloaded upgrades from their site which extends the battery life.  I'm not sure why this information isn't provided upon purchase.  The players stay on "standby" for somewhere like 12 hours until you upgrade and it goes on "standby" for 3 hours.  That's what eats up the battery.  Once I had the upgrade, I was all set.  I don't know what the commotion is about how great the blue light is, but it's nice to have a light.  I did set mine to stay lit a bit longer than the default.  On the positive side, once you figure out the touchpad, the software, the upgrades, and get the warranty..you can really enjoy this player.  This is my first mp3, and I love that i have a stereo now that is so easy to manage and organize and tranport. I replaced the free earbuds (which did have excellent sound) with earbud w/earclips because the buds keep fallling out of my ears.  I have the travel sound speakers by creative that came with it in some promotion.  The music sounds phenomenal.  I also purchased regular speakers and hooked the micro in the living room and it was great during a party.  I then carry it around in my bag when I go anywhere in case I get stuck someplace and then I can listen to anything.  It actually has improved my quality of life!!!!  I also have only been able to get 1000 songs instead of the advertised (with asterik) 2500.  i deliberately went back and changed the settings for burns only on WMA 128, instead of mp3 192, and while that saved quite a bit of space, i ended up with the 1000 songs.    I also can't get any radio stations.  I don't use Outlook, but Palm, and wish i could psynch my calendar with the micro calendar.  In fact, that was part of the reason i justified buying the player-it was a storage disk, palm pilot, tape recorder, radio AND an mp3 player.  but it turns out  not to work for me as a calendar or a radio.    Many snafus, but what an incredible invention.  I'm just hoping it will last for a few years.  And i hope creative keeps on fine-tuning it, and being fast with customer service since they do know their products are problematic.. They have a great website forum where there are very helpful moderators and experienced owners lurking and helping everyone.  You can look up everything you want to know about the battery, touchpad, earphone jack and absolutely everything you can imagine...  Very good product (with lots of potential).  
