<Review ID>8542432
<Product Name>Creative Zen Micro 5 GB MP3 Player Green
<Title>My unit came defective
<Date>Mon Nov 07 00:00:00 CST 2005
<Content>I was looking for something else other than the IPOD when I considered the Zen Micro (ours is 6G) that we sell here at my store. I wanted good battery life, a durable unit, and plenty of space to hold my music under $275.  After much research I decided to buy the Zen Micro 5G which I found at another store for $179. It was defective...  I had previously heard rumors about a lot of problems with Creative's products because of poor design or just general defect. I was hoping to God I wouldn't get something defective, but after all I had heard from people's units crashing after a few months of use, I decided to return this unit instead of exchange.  For one, when I bought it, the touch pad did not work like the manual said. Instead of moving up and down... the up button was sometimes the select key, so when scrolling up I accidentally hit a lot of menu options. To avoid this I just used the lower portion of the pad, it was a pain...  Even worse was when I set up playlists once I got into them itself it changed to another list I could not get out using the Back key. It was EXTREMELY difficult to get to the main menu to change songs... and usually I ended up changing songs and moving the volume and so forth trying to desperately get to the menu.  My remedy was hitting the back key and select key at once REPEATEDLY... doing this about 50 times until it worked was the only way I could get to the playlist or main menu. I was not happy with my unit at all...  The display model at our job works GREAT though and from what I hear some people are happy with the units so far. I was thinking my unit was just defective considering many people have come back saying they've bought other Creative models as well as this one that have had similar problems as well as headjack problems.  I still have faith in Creative and it's reputation, but I would be weary of a lot of defects with their products. The hard drives have crashed after so long, at most a year, and I've seen two Zen Xtras returned withen the past few days which is A LOT considering our store doesn't even sale them.  If you notice with some of their models, the prices has dropped dramatically. For example, the Zen Xtra runs for $217 for a THIRTY GIG hard drive. That is massive for an mp3 player.  I still have some faith in Creative so I'm going to be persistent and try the Zen Sleek as it seems to be a very durable unit and something I'd like to give a try. Hopefully your unit wont be as defective as mine, but you should pay attention to why these prices are so low, and judge for yourself if you think this unit will reach your expectations as it is still a very well designed unit and very attractive looking.  
<Overall>3

