<Title>The zen micro kicks apple nano butt!  
<Date>Wed Sep 28 00:00:00 CST 2005
<Content>If your comparing MP3 players I would either get a Zen Micro or an ipod nano. Everything the nano does the micro does better. the color screen is dumb. looking at pictures on your mp3 player is dumb. having to instal itunes is dumb. that crazy connector on the ipod is dumb. games on an mp3 player are dumb too. PEOPLE! ITS A MP3 PLAYER! If you want pictures get a photo album, if you want games get a psp! If you want a color screen get a plasma tv! the smaller size of the nano is cool but alot of people are breaking them. The Micro gives you better sound quality, bigger harddrive, (great) FM, (good) Recording, and battery replacability for WHEN the battery goes out.I dont care who makes the battery. The only thing the nano has is a little bit better batery life and a solid state hard drive. I still say rotating drives are dependable as long as you dont throw your mp3 player at trees.   I can plug my zen up to my parents computer (with NO creative software on it at all) and swap music, i can switch it to flash drive mode and swap files (I have mine, a 5gig, set up as 4.5gigs music and a .5gig flash drive to store my financial excel stuff and other files. but you can change the setup) This also replaces Flash drives! You can have up to 2 gigs set up, but that means only 3 gigs for songs  I got sony mdr-e10's headphones because the creatives werent cool/good enough. Oh and there is a leather case on ebay from canada with snaps that is very west coast choppers. Its the one thats not krusell. Krusell is for doctors and those silicone things are for children. or you can make a case out of an altoids box, thats also cool. Also motorola makes a wall recharger that has the prongs fold up for the RAZR phone that also recharges the zen without the usb and its tiny too! (the razr and zen have the same 3.7v Lithium battery) The zen takes a USB A - USB mini 5 pin, the same as my cell phone and my camera and radio shack makes a (USB 2.0) retractable cord thats like 4 inches and extends to like 25. But it all depends, they are both good, i just think the micro is better. Plus i got mine refurbished for like 163. creative has them on ebay and i did it that way. mine was 100% brand new. But I also say "Its your money, get what you want!"  
