<Content>This mp3 player is definitely worth the price for its features.  First, the sound quality from the headphones is terrific, considering that they're only little earbud headphones.  I have other pairs of regular headphones from such makers as Sony, and these little headphones have a better sound than most.  The sound is crisp and clear, with the only downfall being that the headphones could use just a little bit more of a bass boost.   Second, the 5gb of room is plenty for me, even with my music library off the player being very large.  I am able to load and delete songs from the player handily using the USB cable and the software that comes with the player (which is very easy to use).  Third, the FM radio, along with its presets, is a terrific idea for an mp3 player, especially knowing that you won't always want to listen to mp3s.  You can also save 32 presets, which is more than most people will be able to use.    Then, as another feature, you can also use the DJ feature to shuffle your entire library.  This is great for times when you need a variety of songs.    This is a terrific player for the money and I would recommend this player to anyone who is looking to stray away from Apple and their iPod, which happens to be mainstreamed only towards iTunes.    
