<Product Name>Creative Zen Micro 5 GB MP3 Player Green
<Title>Great little gadget
<Date>Mon Aug 29 00:00:00 CST 2005
<Content>I've had my Micro for about a month now, I received it as a gift from my boyfriend after he bought his and I mentioned I wanted one too.  I read some people complain about the scroll pad but the truth is that after a couple hours of playing with it (you want to set it to low sensitivity) it's a breeze to use.   No complains about sound quality, its great!  You might want to get a different pair of earbuds as the bundled ones get a bit uncomfortable after wearing them a while.  I was lucky to get the package that had all kinds of accesories but most importantly an AC adapter.  I bought a Rhino skin for my Zen and that keeps it nice and secure plus offers extra grip.  I had to download some firmware from the Creative website in order to get the ZEN explorer application to work.  It was well worth it.  This application lets you rip cds right into the device, create playlists and generally administer the music in your device in a very user friendly environment.  There is another software that is supplied but I never figured out to use it and it was a pain, so the explorer is much easier.  So far, its only frozen once and I think that was my fault because I went click happy.  I had to take out the battery to boot it and after that one time, it hasnt happened again.  It can be a bit slow to respond when you click the FWD or RWD buttons, but maybe that's because I've uploaded so many songs to it.  Design wise, its much more ergonomic that the popular ipods. Even without the Rhino skin, I wasnt afraid it would scratch or lose its nice purple color.  Unlike the mini ipod, the scroll pad is not white and will not get dirty.  The controllers are covered in a non-porous plastic so dirt and grime wont harm them.  The blue backlight is beyond cool, although you might want to set it to a 5 sec lag, as it could use up your battery. I would recommend buying a Rhino Skin to protect your Zen.  Battery life for me is not as advertised.  I get maybe 4-5 hours max.  That was a disappointment.  I give it 4 stars because I had some trouble with the software and the short battery life.  Other than that, I've already recommended this fun device to many friends.  
