<Review ID>3422164
<Product Name>Creative Zen Micro 5 GB MP3 Player Green
<Title>It does its job & It does it well enough
<Date>Fri Sep 09 00:00:00 CST 2005
<Content>After a long and tireful comparison of Zen Micro VS IPod Mini, I ended up buying the Creative Zen Micro.  Well...that may not have been the best choice.  It does what it's supposed to do but it definately has one annoying drawback.  I had the Creative Nomad II a few years ago - which I never had a problem with.  This product's sound quality and other features such as the microphone I greatly enjoyed.  Seeing as the Zen Micro appeared to be an upgraded version, I made my choice.  The Pros: 1) The sound quality.  Even the earbuds it comes with are decent for listening, though I prefer my Sony earbuds as they provide more bass.  There are also several EQ presets or you can set your own.  2) The extra features.  It's a bit annoying to record anything but it works perfectly.  I use Microsoft Outlook so I can easily have a mini version of a PDA.  Though the radio function is lacking in signal, it's a nice option. 3) The program.  I had not one problem with the PC to MP3 Player transfers.  Nor any installation issues. 4) The capacity.  It's plenty for me with my midsize CD collection and various songs purchased from MSN.  I have over 400 songs on it and it isn't even 1/4 full.  The Cons: 1) The player's ability to shut down.  I became horribly frustrated with the stupid little thing when trying to shut it down.  You pull the power button over and the screen says "Shutting Down..." and the backlight goes on, but sometimes that screen never vanishes.  I think I let it sit for 10 minutes and the dang thing didn't shut down.  At least eight times I've had to remove the battery to get it to turn off.  This is horribly annoying when you're in a hurry.  Not to mention that it then goes "Rebuilding library" and makes you sit there even longer.  It returns to the original screen and you have to try shutting it down again.  2) Track playing problems.  Though at the time of transfer my songs went on fine, I find that several of them have glitches that they don't have when played on my computer.  All of a sudden it'll skip a beat or sounds like someone is fast forwarding it.  Though I don't know what is causing this problem, it's not fun when you're into the song.  Overall: I would give it 3 stars because of it's failure to always shut down, but it does its job and it does it well.  This MP3 player does exactly what I wanted it to do - play my music with good sound quality.  4 out of 5  
<Overall>4

