<Product Name>Creative Zen Micro 5 GB MP3 Player Green
<Title>Zen-sational
<Date>Mon Sep 12 00:00:00 CST 2005
<Content>I have had the Creative Zen Micro (5 MB) for about 6 months and in a word, it is outstanding. When researching MP3 players, it really came down to the iPOD vs. the Zen Micro, but the features of the Zen won me over. First and foremost, the sound quality is MUCH better than the iPOD, which after all is why we are listening in the first place. I have listened to both with the same headphones and can hear a significant difference. Second, I found the touch controls and user interface much better and more intuitive than the iPOD. Finally, updates to the firmware have made it simple to buy/download music from ANY service and import into the Zen.   Updates to the software have improved over the months and the end product is fairly straightforward and easy to use. And, despite what one reviewer said, it is really easy to make folders (i.e. playlists) to sort your catalog into multiple groups according to your mood or activity.   I like the feature of having a radio tuner, though I admit I don't use it that much. I have found the signal needs to be fairly strong, so if you are in a more rural area, you may be a little disappointed.   Taking everything together, the Zen Micro is a great buy and is loaded with features for the money (appointment calendar, alarm, etc.) but more than the value, you'll be impressed, like I was, with the sound quality.   
<Overall>5

