<Product Name>Creative Zen Micro 5 GB MP3 Player Green
<Title>I really wanted to like this product, but...
<Date>Fri Aug 26 00:00:00 CST 2005
<Content>I wanted to get an MP3 player that was not an Ipod.  I didn't want to get locked into the Apple file system format. So, after looking into various options I purchased the zen micro.  It worked great for about 3 days after the warranty expired.  Had a problem with the earphone jack. (This is a well documented problem; you may check Creative's web site for more info.)    I sent the Micro back, had to pay $40 since it was out of warranty.  They sent me a refurbished one.  It lasted less than a month.  Got a "Hardware Problem" icon on the player.  Tried various things to revive it.  Contacted e mail support.  They tried to give advice. Nothing worked.  I then contacted them by phone just to get an authorization so I could return the 2nd player.  They said they couldn't talk to me unless I paid $20--just to talk to them...amazing...  Anyway, here I am with a dead micro.  I am still waiting for Creative to get back to me so I can give send them this one back...assuming I want to pay another $40 just for them to look at it.  Should have bought an ipod.  I will steer clear of all Creative Products in the future.      
<Overall>1

